nodes.documentation: @dev An implementation of the IAssetHolder interface. The AssetHolder contract escrows ETH or tokens against state channels. It allows assets to be internally accounted for, and ultimately prepared for transfer from one channel to other channel and/or external destinations, as well as for guarantees to be claimed. Note there is no deposit function and the _transferAsset function is unimplemented; inheriting contracts should implement these functions in a manner appropriate to the asset type (e.g. ETH or ERC20 tokens).
